<TD align="left"><pre>


Output of integer number: The format specification for printing an integer number is    %wd
  where w specifies the minimum field width for the output. However if a number is greater than the specified field
 width,it will be printed in full. Overriding the minimum specification d specifies the value to be printed is an
 integer.
                    The following examples illustrate the output of the number 9876 under different formates:
               Format                                    Output
       printf("%d", 9876)                                9 8 7 6
       printf("%6d",9876)                               S S 9 8 7 6        
       printf("%2d",9876)                               9 8 7 6   
       printf("%-6d",9876)                             9 8 7  6 S S
       printf("%06d",9876)                            0 0 9 8 7 6   
                 
  It is possible to force the printing to be left-justified by placing a minus sign directly after the % character.

Program: The output of integer number under various formats
                         /* printing of integer numbers*/
                         main()
                     { 
                        int m=12345;
                        long n=987654;
                        printf("%d\n",m);
                        printf("%10d\n",m);
                        printf("%010d\n",m);
                        printf("-10d\n",m);
                        printf("%10ld\n",n);
            printf("%10ld \n",-n);
         }
output: 12345
                       12345
             0000012345
             12345
                     987654
                   - 987654   
